def check_for_avgs(s):
    runningaverages = s.rolling(window = 12).mean()
    movingstd = s.rolling(window = 12).std()

    # Plot mobile stats
    orignal_series = plt.plot(s, color = 'orange', label = 'Original Series')
    movingaverage_plot = plt.plot(runningaverages, color = 'green', label = 'Running Average')
    movingstd = plt.plot(movingstd, color = 'brown', label = 'Running Standard Deviation')
    plt.legend(loc = 'best')
    plt.show()

Checking for Stationarity using Dickey Fuller Test¶

In [278]:
def check_for_dickey_fuller_test(s):
    print('\nDickey-Fuller Test Result:\n')
    Dickey_Fuller_Test = adfuller(s, autolag = 'AIC')
    Dickey_Fuller_Test_Output = pd.Series(Dickey_Fuller_Test[0:4], index = ['Test Stats',
                                               'p-value',
                                               'Number of Lags',
                                               'Number of Used Observations'])
    for j, i in Dickey_Fuller_Test[4].items():
        Dickey_Fuller_Test_Output['Critic Value (%s)'%j] = i
    print (Dickey_Fuller_Test_Output)
    print ('\Outputs of Dickey Fuller Test:')
    if Dickey_Fuller_Test_Output[1] > 0.05:
        print('\nSeries is not stationary as p value is greater than 0.05.')
    else:
        print('\nSeries is stationary as p value is less than 0.05.')

Checking for Differencing¶

In [287]:
def check_for_diff(s):
    fig, (ax1, ax2, ax3) = plt.subplots(3)
    ax1.plot(s); ax1.set_title('Original Series'); 
    ax1.axes.xaxis.set_visible(False)
    ax2.plot(s.diff()); 
    ax2.set_title('1st Order Differencing'); 
    ax2.axes.xaxis.set_visible(False)
    ax3.plot(s.diff().diff()); 
    ax3.set_title('2nd Order Differencing')
    plt.show()

In [295]:
def model_performance(test, predictions): 
    mse = (((predictions) - (test)) ** 2).mean()
    mape = np.mean(np.abs((test) - (predictions)) / (test)) * 100
    
    print('MSE : {}'.format(round(mse, 2))+
                  '\nRMSE : {}'.format(round(np.sqrt(mse), 2))+
                  '\nMAPE : {}'.format(round(mape, 2)))

In [303]:
train_arima = train.Transformed_Close.values
test_arima = test.Transformed_Close.values
history = [x for x in train_arima]
predictions = list()
for t in range(len(test_arima)):
    model = ARIMA(history, order=(1,1,0))
    model_fit = model.fit()
    output = model_fit.forecast()
    pred = output[0]
    predictions.append(pred)
    obs = test_arima[t]
    history.append(obs)
    #print('predicted=%.2f, expected=%.2f' % (pred,obs))
    print('predicted=%.2f, expected=%.2f' % (inv_boxcox(pred,lmbda), inv_boxcox(obs,lmbda)))
